{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"870ca652-de82-4aa3-8800-3fd78455d7df","content":"The issue is the file compilation order in the `.fsproj`. In F#, files can only reference modules defined in files listed **before** them. `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`, but is listed first.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_088QYWDbjqns2Y6eaPuUU8","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-8188fa3fe7cf400e955b5e117a7c5c4d/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-8188fa3fe7cf400e955b5e117a7c5c4d/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"274ea0ad-8879-4a68-a2d0-003fef368042","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters - files can only reference types/modules defined in files listed before them in the `.fsproj`. \n\nLooking at the `.fsproj`:\n1. `Services.fs` is listed first\n2. `Domain.fs` is listed second\n3. `Program.fs` is listed third\n\nBut `Services.fs` opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`, which is defined in `Domain.fs`. Since `Domain.fs` comes after `Services.fs` in the compile order, the compiler can't find `BrokenOrder.Domain` when compiling `Services.fs`.\n\nThe fix is to reorder the `<Compile>` items so that `Domain.fs` comes before `Services.fs`:\n\n\n1. `Domain.fs`\n2. `Services.fs`\n3. `Program.fs`","outputTokens":480,"requestId":"280D:19764A:1B4999B:1E59F3B:69FA8FEA"},"id":"1574bb1b-80d2-420c-82a3-34d41331571c","timestamp":"2026-05-06T00:48:50.784Z","parentId":"e6c33451-976c-4979-9378-212a335e2841"}
